.TH "try_to_unlazy" 9 "try_to_unlazy" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
try_to_unlazy \- try to switch to ref-walk mode.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" try_to_unlazy
.BI "(struct nameidata *nd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nd" 12
nameidata pathwalk data
.SH "RETURN"
true on success, false on failure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
try_to_unlazy attempts to legitimize the current nd->path and nd->root
for ref-walk mode.
Must be called from rcu-walk context.
Nothing should touch nameidata between \fBtry_to_unlazy\fP failure and
\fBterminate_walk\fP.
